author: scheu
msg: Added the support for complexTypes (beans) that use <extension base="type"> to extend another type.
This change resulted in an additional Type parameter to the JavaComplexTypeWriter constructor.
The new parameter is the Type of the base class or null if no base class.
Changes were made to SchemaTypes to get the extension base (and skip over extension base).
Changes were also made to Utils.getNestedTypes to also process the extended base and types within the
extended base.
To test these changes I modified the MultiRef testcase.  The existing node complex Type
was split into nodebase and derived node types.
